R, Schneider RA, Rubin SB, Matari&#x107; MJ, McDuff DJ, Jones Bell M. The opportunities and risks of large language models in mental health. JMIR Ment Health.  Jul 29, 2024;11:e59479. [<a target="_blank" href="https://dx.doi.org/10.2196/59479">CrossRef</a>] [<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=Retrieve&amp;db=PubMed&amp;list_uids=39105570&amp;dopt=Abstract" target="_blank">Medline</a>]</span></li><li><span id="ref8">Robinson A, Flom M, Forman-Hoffman VL,  et al. Equity in digital mental health interventions in the United States: where to next? J Med Internet Res.  Sep 24, 2024;26:e59939. [<a target="_blank" href="https://dx.doi.org/10.2196/59939">CrossRef</a>] [<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=Retrieve&amp;db=PubMed&amp;list_uids=39316436&amp;dopt=Abstract" target="_blank">Medline</a>]</span></li><li><span id="ref9">Wang X, Sanders HM, Liu Y,  et al. ChatGPT: promise and challenges for deployment in low- and middle-income countries. Lancet Reg Health West Pac.  Dec 2023;41:100905. [<a target="_blank" href="https://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.lanwpc.2023.100905">CrossRef</a>] [<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=Retrieve&amp;db=PubMed&amp;list_uids=37731897&amp;dopt=Abstract" target="_blank">Medline</a>]</span></li><li><span id="ref10">Creed TA, Salama L, Slevin R,  et al. Enhancing the quality of cognitive behavioral therapy in community mental health through artificial intelligence generated fidelity feedback (Project AFFECT): a study protocol. BMC Health Serv Res.  Sep 20, 2022;22(1):1177. [<a target="_blank" href="https://dx.doi.org/10.1186/s12913-022-08519-9">CrossRef</a>] [<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=Retrieve&amp;db=PubMed&amp;list_uids=36127689&amp;dopt=Abstract" target="_blank">Medline</a>]</span></li><li><span id="ref11">Omar M, Soffer S, Charney AW, Landi I, Nadkarni GN, Klang E. Applications of large language models in psychiatry: a systematic review. Front Psychiatry.   2024;15:1422807. [<a target="_blank" href="https://dx.doi.org/10.3389/fpsyt.2024.1422807">CrossRef</a>] [<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=Retrieve&amp;db=PubMed&amp;list_uids=38979501&amp;dopt=Abstract" target="_blank">Medline</a>]</span></li><li><span id="ref12">Wang C, Liu S, Yang H, Guo J, Wu Y, Liu J. Ethical considerations of using ChatGPT in health care. J Med Internet Res.  Aug 11, 2023;25:e48009. [<a target="_blank" href="https://dx.doi.org/10.2196/48009">CrossRef</a>] [<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=Retrieve&amp;db=PubMed&amp;list_uids=37566454&amp;dopt=Abstract" target="_blank">Medline</a>]</span></li><li><span id="ref13">Zhang G, Jin Q, Zhou Y,  et al. Closing the gap between open source and commercial large language models for medical evidence summarization. NPJ Digital Med.  Sep 9, 2024;7(1):239. [<a target="_blank" href="https://dx.doi.org/10.1038/s41746-024-01239-w">CrossRef</a>] [<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=Retrieve&amp;db=PubMed&amp;list_uids=39251804&amp;dopt=Abstract" target="_blank">Medline</a>]</span></li><li><span id="ref14">Fang C, Wu Y, Fu W,  et al. How does ChatGPT-4 preform on non-English national medical licensing examination? An evaluation in Chinese language. PLOS Digital Health.  Dec 2023;2(12):e0000397. [<a target="_blank" href="https://dx.doi.org/10.1371/journal.pdig.0000397">CrossRef</a>] [<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=Retrieve&amp;db=PubMed&amp;list_uids=38039286&amp;dopt=Abstract" target="_blank">Medline</a>]</span></li><li><span id="ref15">Ando K, Sato M, Wakatsuki S,  et al. A comparative study of English and Japanese ChatGPT responses to anaesthesia-related medical questions. BJA Open.  Jun 2024;10:100296. [<a target="_blank" href="https://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.bjao.2024.100296">CrossRef</a>] [<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=Retrieve&amp;db=PubMed&amp;list_uids=38975242&a